@0 = ~The Final Battle with Bodhi.

While I had feared for some time that Bodhi's final revenge on me would be to take away Tashia forever, it seems that the information in the lorebook was right...  Amaunator's idol has restored Tashia not only to life, but has removed the vampiric curse from her, as well.~

@1 = ~The Final Battle with Bodhi.

Bodhi has turned Tashia into a vampire!  Or... or very nearly.  The process may not have been completed in the short time Bodhi has had her.  Hopefully something can be done or I will have lost her.  Perhaps the elven war sage might know some way of restoration... or Elhan...~

@2 = ~The Final Battle with Bodhi

Bodhi appeared in an ambush shortly before I reached her haven, warning me that she was aware of my pursuit and stealing from me the one person that is dearest to my heart: Tashia.  Before she vanished and unleashed more of her undead creations upon me, Bodhi warned me that if I continue I will lose even more than I thought possible.  I cannot give up on the Rhynn Lanthorn... but now the life and immortal soul of the one I love is at stake, as well!~
@3    = ~(Tashia breathes deeply as the ship comes to a full stop, and grabbing part of the rigging, she breathes in deeply, her chest swelling with the air.)~
@4    = ~Finally, land. I'll be so glad to get out of this salt air and into a warm tub...~
@5    = ~(Taking a deep breath, you notice the red flush of her cheeks, vivacious sparkle in her jade green eyes, the weariness from your sea voyage gone from her exuberant face. Between the spray of the sea and the humidity of the air, her robe clinging tightly to her body, showing her thin, tight figure, hugging her small, round breasts, rising and falling with the rocking of the boat.)~
@6    = ~(Tashia smiles, and her lips twists up slightly)
I am first mouth, then hand
Aired together for a message
That always means the same
I am sent as the crow would go
But although some pretend to catch me,
My fate is to fly forever, Never to arrive...~
@7    = ~Could it be the wind, carrying your words through the air? (Walk over to her, and run your fingers through a few links of her hair after you answer)~
@8    = ~(Smile at Tashia, kiss your palm, and blow it towards her cheek)~
@9    = ~Perhaps it is a kiss, blown through the air...~
@10   = ~Perhaps it is the wind, carrying your voice...~
@11   = ~I don't really know...~
@12   = ~(Tashia leans back into your hand, her eyes closing, a slight pleasant hum escapes from her lips) That is close, but not quite. The answer is a blown kiss.~
@13   = ~(Her eyes snap open, and she pulls away from you) Um, let's get going...~
@14   = ~(Tashia's smile grows larger and she moves, catching the kiss with a swift hand, then bringing it up, and pressing it to her cheek.)~
@15   = ~(Tashia gives a slight chuckle, her face staring fondly at yours, when she suddenly turns her head aside, cheeks burning bright red.)~
@16   = ~Sorry, we still have to finish your quest, don't we?~
@17   = ~(Tashia's face seems to lose some of its exuberance, although she still bears a slight smile) Correct. The answer is a blown kiss.~
@18   = ~(Tashia glances over the horizon) Let's get going...~
@19   = ~(Tashia's face loses a small bit of its vitality, but she shakes her head) No, it is a blown kiss. But you weren't too far off...~
@20   = ~(She gives a last glance at the sea, and then turns around) I guess we should get going...~
@21   = ~(Tashia's mouth widens, and she chuckles) Well, they say being too long at sea can addle one's wits...~
@22   = ~(She turns around, and looks out over the sea, a sigh escaping her lips) Well, looks like it's time to get back to business...~
@23   = ~(Tashia walks forward in the darkness, the warmth of her breath creating a slight fog, as she balls her fists together, then slowly lets them go. She takes one tentative step, then another forward, before turning to look at you.)~
@24   = ~Mine is the ungloved
pulsing fingertip

The shroud, the interface
of brittle leaves

Mine is the cruel purity
that snaps all iron,

Sends your warm breath
biting backwards

I am the splintered rainbow
locked in ice...~
@25   = ~(Place a reassuring hand on Tashia's shoulder) Tashia? Are you alright?~
@26   = ~(Place a reassuring hand on Tashia's shoulder) Is it frost?~
@27   = ~(Place a reassuring hand on Tashia's shoulder) Is it death?~
@28   = ~(Push Tashia forward by placing your hand on the back of her shoulder) Pull yourself together, woman. Danger surrounds us, and you want to recite poetry in the darkness.~
@29   = ~(Tashia turns around, and she squeezes your hand) I'm alright, or I will be once we get out of here. Funny, I never thought I would miss the surface so greatly. Here... it's just cold, unfeeling stone beneath my feet. I feel... disjointed... if that makes sense...~
@30   = ~(She shrugs, removing your hand from her shoulder) Let's get out of here. Who knows what dwells in the shadows...~
@31   = ~(Tashia reaches up and squeezes your hand) That is correct. Frost is the answer.~
@32   = ~(Tashia stands close to you, drawing comfort from your nearness, whispering) I guess I didn't believe the stories about how cold, how dark the Underdark is. Of course, I didn't believe I would ever come here...~
@33   = ~(She leans in closer, her other hand absent-mindedly grabbing your free hand and she gives a contented sigh.)~
@34   = ~(Tashia then blushes, as she notices just how close she is to you, and she quickly pulls away) Umm... let's get going. We still have a lot to do...~
@35   = ~(Tashia reaches, and squeezes your hand, giving a slight chuckle) Well that is a suitably morbid answer. Given our surroundings, I guess I might say the same thing...~
@36   = ~(She removes your hand from her shoulder, a strange, measuring look on her face, whispering) Heh, the answer I was looking for was frost. I don't know about you, but I'm getting a bit cold...~
@37   = ~(She sighs, and moves forward, her anxiety overcome) Let's go... I am already starting to miss the sun...~
@38   = ~(Tashia looks slightly hurt, but she shifts her stance, walking toward the front of the group) Right you are, we have better things to do in the darkness... like snapping at those around us.~
@39   = ~(Tashia seems oddly quiet after you've rescued Imoen. In fact, when your back is turned, you definitely get the feeling of being watched, and when you turn your head to glance around, you see Tashia jerk her head to focus her attention on something else.)~
@40   = ~(Ignore her. If she's got anything on her mind, she'll let you know.)~
@41   = ~(Go up to her, resting a hand on her shoulder) Is something wrong Tashia?~
@42   = ~(Tashia gives a wan smile) Oh I'm alright. I was just doing some remembering, that's all. You're close to her, aren't you? Imoen I mean...~
@43   = ~Close? Don't make me laugh... she's been a constant pain in the ass ever since we left Candlekeep. I tried to send her home way back when... but she insisted on following me and look where it got her...~
@44   = ~Of course we are close. She was the sister I never had. Well, growing up an orphan and all that. Don't get me wrong... Gorion was a good man, but let's just say that his idea of a good time was to curl up with a good book. Heh, sometimes I wonder how he could stand the two of us, let alone just myself growing up...~
@45   = ~(Tashia's eyes flash angrily) Is that all she is to you? Is that the only reason you have her around?~
@46   = ~(Her eyes narrow) Is that how you see me? As some kind of camp follower? Someone to sate your lust with? Someone who will take an arrow for you when we're ambushed?~
@47   = ~Of course. You know what my quest is. It's paramount that Irenicus is stopped, at all costs. As it is, I stand the best chance of taking him down, but even I can get taken out any time. The more people in the party, the greater the individual chances of our survival.~
@48   = ~(smirk) No, I'm just kidding. If that's all I thought of her, would I have risked life and limb to come rescue her?~
@49   = ~(Tashia's face grows livid) To hell with you! I am not going to be some kind of damn target for an arrogant, insufferable bastard like you...~
@50   = ~I should have known better... you Bhaalspawn are all the same... the next time we meet... we are enemies...~
@51   = ~(Tashia shakes her head forlornly) I didn't find that at all humorous... I like Imoen, and you really shouldn't say a thing like that... not with all she's gone through...~
@52   = ~(Tashia steps back, and looks at you, as if making a decision, and nods to herself.)~
@53   = ~(Tashia smiles at your words) Heh, well I think all parents are like that. My foster parents were exactly the same way. Why, I remember the day we all climbed to the roof, pretending we could fly. I learned that day I wasn't an Avariel...~
@54   = ~(Tashia blushes as she subconsciously rubs her backside) Let's just say I think I have a good idea what an ass-kicking feels like...~
@55   = ~Heh... that's pretty good Tashia. Yeah, sometimes I wonder how we ever managed to finish childhood myself. Why, I remember that Phlydia, she was one of the monks at Candlekeep, had her birthday coming up... early spring now that I think of it... I completely forgot about it until Imoen mentioned it. Well, I suddenly had a brainstorm. I decided to pick a bunch of wildflowers for her! I found some nice flowers, and bound them together, but I also saw this shrub that had some pretty red leaves...~
@56   = ~(shake your head) Well, I never really had too many episodes growing up truth be known...~
@57   = ~(Tashia's grin goes wide) Heh... well, you know, girls always do like flowers...~
@58   = ~(She lays her hand on your shoulder, and winks at you, whispering) If you ever have an itch to scratch... I will... relieve you...~
@59   = ~(Tashia pulls on your arm, whispering into your ear) Can you give me a few minutes? There is something further I must do...~
@60   = ~(She walks a little ways away from you, kneeling on the ground, and she starts to dig in the ground, her eyes closed, as she murmurs...)~
@61   = ~I commend the soul of one long lost
Into thine embrace, She of the Luminous Cloud

He was lost in the winter
Dwelling in isolation

He would not see
That autumn is not
Cold enough to
Destroy desire...~
@62   = ~Memories so old
He would waken
Darkness within
Driving him beneath the sky

He did not want to die
Bound in greed and madness
Conscience and sadness
Bound deep within

I beseech of you,
Daughter of the Nightsky
Lead him to the coming spring...~
@63   = ~(As the last of the words come from her lips, Tashia reaches into her robe, pulling out a small silvery locket from her pocket, and she raises it to her lips, giving it a kiss, before putting it in the hole, covering it with the freshly dug soil. A single, silvery tear courses down her face, and dots the earth.)~
@64   = ~(She whispers) May Sehanine Moonbow help your soul, Arilistan...~
@65   = ~(With a sigh, Tashia rises, and she leans into the crook of your arm, her arm entwined in yours) Okay, let's go.~
@66   = ~(Tashia starts becoming more and more like her own self again, after the events that Arilistan forced upon her, and her subsequent resurrection. However, you definitely catch slight glimpses from the corner of your eye, as Tashia glances fondly at you, and then turns her head to return to the matter at hand.)~
@67   = ~(As you travel, Tashia moves closer as well, occasionally slipping her hand into yours, and in one such instance, she pulls you aside from the group, momentarily, and says) I never thought I would have fallen in love again... it's almost as if it was god sent.~
@68   = ~(Tashia's eyes open wide, as she whispers) Maybe... goddess sent?~
@69   = ~(Shaking her head, her long blonde hair momentarily covering her eyes, she bites her lip deep in thought, obviously thinking on the matter, as she mutters) It just could be... and even if not... I shouldn't take any chances...~
@70   = ~(Tashia smiles at you) Would you mind humoring me for just a second?~
@71   = ~ (Tashia raises your right palm to face hers, then your left, her feet paralleling yours. She starts to kiss you, first along the length of your hand, starting with the tip of your fingers, slowly making her way to your palm. Her other hand traces along your other hand, as she says...)~
@72   = ~I voice my appreciation
O, Lady Goldheart
For granting your blessing unto me

I am saved,
Saved from false assumption
Saved from being lost.~
@73   = ~(By this point, Tashia is kissing along your shoulder, taking a special moment to kiss the crook of your shoulder and neck, her other hand now entwined with yours, lowered to your sides.)~
@74   = ~I am unfettered,
Freed from isolation
Freed from bondage.

I am whole
Healed from loneliness
Healed of separation.~
@75   = ~(By this moment, Tashia is pressing her lips firmly onto your own, her soft and pliant body pressed up next to yours. When she pulls away, you see that her cheeks are blushing bright red.)~
@76   = ~(A breeze swirls amidst the two of you, and a soft tinkling of bells rings within your hearing, meant for you alone, as she whispers) Thank you Hanali Celanil...~
@77   = ~(You wake up in the wee hours of the day, just before the sun has crested the horizon, allowing its warm rays to caress the earth in anticipation of a new day. You find Tashia curled near you, her body allowing yours to shield hers, and she mumbles) Just a few more minutes...~
@78   = ~(Giving a quick glance over the rest of the campsite, you see that the other members of your party are enjoying their own rest from the drudgeries of the previous night. Tashia shifts near you again, and she mumbles a little more) Love... you...~
@79   = ~(Continue to lie by Tashia's side, wrapping an arm protectively around her side, feeling the chill on her back slowly warming up as you press in close to her. She shivers initially, her breath quickening momentarily, and then her body presses close into yours as a result, and you hear a soft, satisfied sigh escape from her lips.)~
@80   = ~(Deciding to wake up your beloved with a sweet surprise, you envelop her body from behind, sliding your left arm along Tashia's, stroking her skin in soothing circles, while you gently nibble the tip of her fine, angular ear. There is a shift in Tashia's form as she pushes deeper into you, and you hear a small rumble build up in the back of her throat.)~
@81   = ~(Tashia continues to rest easily next to you, but then you feel her body tense as she shifts position, and you find yourself staring into her crystalline jade eyes, a small smile quirking her lips, and she whispers) Hmm... I could get used to this...~
@82   = ~(She leans forward, kissing you gently on your cheek, and then proceeds to sit up, pulling the blanket across her lean shoulders. Grasping your hand in hers, she barely stifles a yawn, and says) So what now?~
@83   = ~(Clasp her hand in yours) Would you mind... watching the sunrise with me?~
@84   = ~(sigh) This is pleasant, but we really should get going. The day won't get shorter just by lazing about.~
@85   = ~(Tashia's features soften, and her smile brightens) Of course I will...~
@86   = ~(Clasping her hand in yours, she leans in so close to you that your nose is slightly tickled by her hair, though it smells faintly of peach, as well as the leaves of the forest. As her hand holds yours, you feel the faint pulse of her heart through your grasping hands, but as she leans back and lays the back of her head on your shoulder, you feel her pulse quicken, until it matches your own, and it seems as if you both are sharing the same heartbeat, and your breathing synchronizes, sharing the same moment as one.)~
@87   = ~(The sun slowly climbs over the distance, and in this instant, as the rays slowly warm the both of you, Tashia slowly stands. Extending her hand to you, beckoning for you to stand with her. As you do so, she stands on her tip toes, and her soft lips press against yours once more, her arms drawing you in close. After a few breathless moments, she parts from you, a gasp escaping her lungs.)~
@88   = ~(Her eyes stare adoringly at you as she says) I could get used to this...~
@89   = ~(A look of disappointment crosses Tashia's face, and when she next speaks, you catch anger in her voice) You woke me up just to tell me to get going?~
@90   = ~(Her eyes dart across the other resting forms of the party, as she growls) You might want to make sure that everyone else is up before you wake me up.~
@91   = ~(Tashia rises and starts to roll up her bedroll as she grumbles about taking her foot and giving someone a solid kick in the ass the next time they wake her up early.)~
@92   = ~(A moan escapes from the back of Tashia's throat, and she shifts once more, this time lying on her side. Her hand rises up to caress your face, and her face rises to meet yours, caressing your lips with hers. Then softly under her breath, she whispers) Oh, Arilistan...~
@93   = ~(As she says his name, her eyes quickly open, and she falls away from you, her eyes now wide open, her hand falling from your cheek, covering her mouth, as she says) Oh <CHARNAME>... I'm... I didn't mean... I mean, I'm...~
@94   = ~(Tashia's face turns bright red, as she turns her head, and you see a tear roll down her cheek, and she doesn't raise her face to look at you.)~
@95   = ~(Anger rises deep within you, and your face contorts into a grimace) Arilistan? Even now, after all we've been through, you still want him, is that it? I shouldn't be surprised, even after all I did for you... the minute he showed up, you went rushing off into his arms, not even giving me a never-you-mind. Was that it, maybe? You still have feelings for Arilistan, but after he played you false, you decided to settle... for me?~
@96   = ~(Sorrow travels through your body, and you sit down, placing your head between your hands, as you quietly ask her) Tashia, you know I love you, and I understand that you would still have some feelings for Arilistan... I guess I want to know... when you said you loved me, were you telling the truth? I mean, you were in a bad state when we helped you, maybe it was relief you felt, not love...~
@97   = ~(Tashia's eyes go shiny for a moment, as she walks forward, taking your hands in hers, and she gives a soft kiss on your lips) <CHARNAME>, I wouldn't play with your feelings that way.~
@98   = ~(Her eyes downcast for just a second, she looks back into your face, softness and caring suffusing her countenance) I'm sorry this happened, but you are the only one for me. If I had any doubts as to your true feelings about me, they were quelled when you resurrected me.~
@99   = ~(She smiles tenderly, leaning into your hand, as she says) It is still new to me, so forgive me if I stumble a bit. But I know what I feel, and that is that I love you...~
@100  = ~(Tashia's eyes flash angrily at your allegations, and she hisses) It's not like that at all. Damn it, I didn't mean to say that at all... but if you can't believe that it was just a slip of the tongue, maybe you aren't the man I thought you were...~
@101  = ~(Tashia's face hardens) I didn't mean to hurt you, but you know what he was to me, what he meant to me. I'm sorry, part of that slipped through.~
@102  = ~(Tashia seems to be on the verge of tears as this last comes tumbling out of her mouth, but she stands resolute) But if you can't forgive me...~
@103  = ~(You quell your inner turmoil, and you look Tashia deep in her hesitant jade green eyes, and you tell her with no uncertainty) Of course I forgive you. I love you, I just needed to be certain...~
@104  = ~(You shake your head, your wound still raw from her inadvertent betrayal) I would never have done that to you Tashia. It's obvious to me that you aren't ready for another relationship... Maybe the next time you say you 'love' someone, you might wish to make sure that is the case.~
@105  = ~(Tashia's face contorts with fury, and she says) You bastard, you think that I was just lying about my emotions?~
@106  = ~(The anger then drains from her, as she says) If you can't even forgive one mistake, then it's probably just as well we split up.~
@107  = ~(She looks at you sadly, then turns around to pack away her bedroll, ignoring any further entreaties to speak.)~
@108  = ~(Tashia gives a great yawn, and she cocks her head) I'm getting tired of cold rations.  Would you be up for another riddle contest? This time, the winner would be the one to make dinner. A hot dinner too...~
@109  = ~Why don't you give the riddles a rest for the moment, Tashia? Besides, cold rations aren't all that bad. But I promise we will get something hot the next inn we come to.~
@110  = ~Sure, that doesn't sound like too bad an idea. Okay, lay your riddle on me.~
@111  = ~Hmmm... a riddle contest sounds good. But let's raise the stakes from just making dinner to something a bit higher.~
@112  = ~(Tashia frowns slightly, and says) Fine, have it your way.~
@113  = ~(Her voice drops to a low grumble) I mean, the damn biscuits are hard enough to hammer nails. And I'm getting tired of cutting off the green portion of the salted pork.~
@114  = ~(Tashia smiles, and closes her eyes) 
At the sound of me, men may dream 
Or stamp their feet 
At the sound of me, women may laugh 
Or sometimes weep. What am I?~
@115  = ~A story.~
@116  = ~Victory.~
@117  = ~Music.~
@118  = ~A story? Well, that is close. After all, stories may bring several emotions to bear on one's heart, whether a well-written love story to wonderful tales of bravery to chortles of mirth. And they certainly may inspire one to dream, but stomp one's feet? No, the answer you seek is music. But as I said, that was a very good try.~
@119  = ~(Tashia smiles, as she says) Looks like you get to make dinner tonight... I look forward to it.~
@120  = ~(Tashia harrumphs) So that is the way it is going to be, then?~
@121  = ~(Her smile grows larger, as she adds) Well, I will keep you to that promise, then. I do suggest that you keep some extra coin in your purse.~
@122  = ~(Tashia tentatively grabs a roll, and then smiles) Hey, this is really good.~
@123  = ~(She grabs another one and another one, adding) I'll be honest, I don't normally care for sausage. But this is fairly good...~
@124  = ~(Tashia stands on tiptoe, and lays a kiss on the side of your cheek) A girl could get accustomed to this...~
@125  = ~That is a rather good guess. I will be honest, I was thinking of 'Music' but I can see where victory may inspire dreams. And of course, women may laugh or cry, or both. Upon achieving victory, their emotions finally getting release. And when winning, I imagine one would raise a clamor, especially if a soldier, and stomping one's foot could do it.~
@126  = ~Wow, you must have heard this one before, music it is. Well, you just go attend to other matters, I shall get supper ready soon enough.~
@127  = ~(She heads off, talking quietly to herself) Hmm... he's getting better at this. I'm really going to have to think of a tougher one.~
@128  = ~(Tashia quickly makes a few snare traps, and goes about looking at the foliage around the location of camp, and she brightens perceptibly as she finds evidence of wild mint and sage. There is sound that comes from the direction of her simple snare, and she brings back two rabbits. She lays them down as she disrupts her other snare traps and then comes back to skin the rabbits.)~
@129  = ~(As the rabbits are roasting on a wooden stick over a fire, you see her taking a traveling tin full of water, mixing in the plants she found and ground up and putting a glaze over the rabbits.)~
@130  = ~(As she finishes, Tashia looks at you expectantly) How is it?~
@131  = ~This is actually pretty good, especially the rabbit. Heh, and while I'm not to fond of gruel, the honey really makes it enjoyable to eat. Better than I can do at any rate.~
@132  = ~Well, if this is the best you can do, I think it's a guarantee you won't be cooking for the party anymore. I would heartily recommend that you stay away from any kitchen you might be near.~
@133  = ~(Tashia blushes shyly) Thanks, I'm glad you like it. I know that I didn't really have a lot of choice or time. Heh, even back at home, I was usually the last one asked to cook. My step-mother would swear that I could burn water.~
@134  = ~(She reaches up, and kisses you on the lips, a slight dab of honey still on her lips and her fingers entwine your hair. When she lets go, she has a mischievous glint in her eyes) Sweets for the sweet, eh?~
@135  = ~(Tashia glares) I would like to see you do better than this. Oh wait, you didn't. I guess that will show me for trying to make a friendly wager with you.~
@136  = ~(She flounces away, growling to herself) I swear, sometimes I don't know why I bother.~
@137  = ~(Tashia, arches an eyebrow, her interest aroused) Okay, and what stakes are you wanting to wager?~
@138  = ~On second thought, dinner sounds just fine. Bring on the riddle...~
@139  = ~How about a massage? All this traveling does give us plenty of kinks.~
@140  = ~Sex and plenty of it...~
@141  = ~(Tashia looks at you with disgust) You know, just when I think I get to know you, you pull something like this. If you are in such great need of female companionship, go hire yourself a two-bit whore... preferably one with boils.~
@142  = ~(Tashia smiles, and closes her eyes as she considers the offer, and then opens them again) Okay, it's a deal.~
@143  = ~When set loose I fly away
Never so curse
As when I go astray
What am I?~
@144  = ~An arrow?~
@145  = ~A tongue?~
@146  = ~Hope?~
@147  = ~An arrow... close, but the only way it would be a curse for going astray is if you happened to hit someone by accident. The answer was 'Tongue'.~
@148  = ~(Tashia stretches her arms out, and then turns with her back to you, and she sighs contentedly as you put your hands to her soft flesh...~
@149  = ~You're really getting much better at this, aren't you? Well, turn around... a bet is a bet, after all.~
@150  = ~(As you follow her instructions, you feel her soft, but firm hands work on the muscles around your neck, gently kneading one moment then pressing firmly another moment. Then you feel a small moment of heat prickle your body, your muscles tensing suddenly, then going lax.)~
@151  = ~(As she leans in close, you feel two more presses on your back, and then find Tashia hugging you close from behind, the scent of her lilac hair filling your nostrils. Her hand starts to trace a design on your back) Feeling better?~
@152  = ~(Tashia looks at you with an odd look in her eyes) Hope? That is an odd turn of thought. I guess I can see what you are talking about, for to lose hope. And yet, without hope one might as well turn over and die. Well, the answer I was looking for was 'Tongue' actually.~
@153  = ~(She looks speculatively at you, and coming to a decision, she adds) I think that I will take a rain check on that back rub...~
@154  = ~(Tashia hums a nameless tune, a smile on her lips, and when she comes close, she deliberately bumps into you. Her smile widens as she gives your buttocks a tight squeeze before encircling you in a tight hug, the fingers of her left hand tracing a circular pattern in the small of your back.)~
@155  = ~Hmm... my mother warned me about men like you.~
@156  = ~(Her eyes sparkle as she reaches up, pressing her lips closely to yours, then withdraws.)~
@157  = ~Seriously, I think my foster parents would like you. Heh, even though they might have a thing or two to say about your table manners.~
@158  = ~Well, it's obvious that you must not think too highly of your foster parents. I mean, it is a long way from the Ten Towns, now isn't it? In fact, didn't you say that you and all your foster siblings left? Just where are they? Oh, and maybe it hasn't occurred to you by now, but I am getting tired of hearing your incessant banter. This gabble about your parents is just the longest string. Here is something to consider: silence is golden.~
@159  = ~What do you mean my table manners? I mean, how else are you supposed to let the chef know that you enjoy his cooking, other than by belching out loud and strong. Besides, how was I supposed to know that you weren't supposed to blow your nose on the tablecloth? How was I supposed to know that one doesn't sniff the pepper?~
@160  = ~Thanks Tashia, you really know how to cheer me up. You know, in all the time we've been together, you really haven't talked about your foster parents before now. What were they like? That is, if you don't mind telling me. I mean, they were an important part of your life, and if we get a chance to meet them... I wouldn't like to be an embarrassment to you.~
@161  = ~(Tashia's eyes snap open, and she angrily retorts) What the hell brought that on?!?~
@162  = ~(Letting go of your hands, Tashia curls up her fists, and in that moment, you see the collected energy of her wrath directing magic into her hands) You know what? Forget it, I don't really care what brought that on.~
@163  = ~(Tashia uncurls her fists, and the energy bleeds off into the environment) I guess I was a fool to fall for you. If all you wanted was someone to sit there and look pretty, I'm sure you could have bought any number of whores with all the gold you've spent up to now.~
