@167  = ~(Drawing your body close, she drapes her arms over your shoulders, lowering your hand to her hip, and her smile becomes more intimate) Heh, it is a bit funny, though. When I am with you, my thoughts do occasionally turn to thoughts of family...~
@168  = ~Family? But, I thought you wanted to travel, didn't you? I mean, that's why you are in Amn, rather than in Ten Towns, right?~
@169  = ~Children? Do you honestly see us having children now? ...I'm sorry, that probably came out sounding harsher than I intended. It's just that having a family is a big step, and I think that we really need to discuss it further before we make a decision that will irrevocably change our lives. Please don't be angry.~
@170  = ~Family? Don't make me laugh. If it's family you want, then maybe it's just best that we stop this here and now. What would I do with a mewling brat? In case you haven't noticed, our lifestyle isn't very conducive to raising children, and I am not the type to settle down, especially to raise a bunch of rugrats.~
