@181  = ~(Tashia's smile grows large, and she says) Well, we really haven't been together that long. But I wouldn't mind telling you about them...~
@182  = ~(She gives a sultry laugh) Well, my foster mother Abigail, she is a kind woman. Very industrious, in fact. Heck, sometimes I still wonder how she manages to get everything done. She has a predilection for cats. I mean, she has a whole shelf devoted to small cat figurines. She calls it her silly little hobby, but I remember one birthday when all of us managed to buy her a ceramic kitten. We accidentally dropped it, breaking its ear... but you would have thought we gave her the greatest treasure in the world. There was always something over the firepot, I don't recall any of us going to bed hungry. Even if we were grounded, she usually snuck something to us.~
@183  = ~Roald, he was our stepfather. Heh, he was fun to be around, too much so in fact. If it wasn't for Abigail, I think he would have let the farm detioriate. I don't mean that in a bad way, he was always a dreamer. All the stories he told... I think he always wanted to be an adventurer, but he settled for being a farmer. He always seemed to have time for us.~
@184  = ~(Tashia seems hesitant, as she says) Seems kind of boring... now that I put it that way, doesn't it?~
@185  = ~Not at all. They took in several orphaned children, and from the sounds of it they gave you a happy childhood. I would have been proud to call them parents, much as you do. Heh, you want dull, though, then you should have met Gorion. I mean, I guess it wasn't exactly his fault. How many scholars have a clue on how to raise a child, let alone in an isolated place like Candlekeep. Still, I miss him, even now.~
@186  = ~Tashia, what do you expect me to say? You won't hear me say anything insulting about your parents. I fell in love with the woman they raised, didn't I? Besides, whatever else we may think of our parents... we do love them, don't we? So, when all this is done, would you like to see your parents again?~
