@384  = ~(Turn around, embrace Tashia tightly in your arms, and laugh) Of course I will always be there for you. You would have to kill me to pry myself away from you. Heh, I truly don't know what I intend to do after all this is over. I may decide to go back and find out more about my people. One thing I do know that is my blood is too restless to settle down for long...and I'll be honest, I like the challenges I face. It keeps me strong. Life is a test, and it is up to us to face it on our own terms. Of course, being strong means both mentally and physically. Perhaps you would like to help me flex my mind by telling me one of your riddles...~
@385  = ~Oh, I don't know what my future holds, other than that you are the most important part of it. Heh, you know, I never really felt comfortable in the confines of Candlekeep. I felt caged, trapped. I always took pride in my own abilities, my own strengths. In some ways, magic just seemed like a cheat, and an unreliable one at best. So imagine my surprise when I found that the most important person in my life is also the most magical...~
