@496  = ~(Tashia finally lets loose with a laugh, and she twists in your arms, holding them close to her chest, and slightly sways, as she relishes being in your presence. She closes her eyes seductively before murmuring pleasantly) Don't think future evasions will be so easy...~
@497  = ~(Tashia looks at you, and her shoulders seem to sag a little) You're looking forward to this, aren't you? I mean, the challenge of running the guildhouse. No, don't deny it or confirm it, I can see it in your eyes. But even more than that, I can see the anticipation of the conflicts to come.~
@498  = ~(She sighs, and shakes her head, as she says) I guess I shouldn't be too surprised. It's the taint within you. Maybe it was foolish of me to think that it would have been any different with you.~
@499  = ~(She leans in and gives a last kiss on your cheek, and then says) As you said, we can't live in the past, but I don't want to just live for today without any thought for tomorrow.~
@500  = ~(As she moves away, she sighs, and says to herself) That's what you get for losing yourself in the moment...~
@501  = ~Heh, you really have turned the playhouse around, haven't you? Now that you are a success, though, it makes me wonder about us... about me. Maybe I'm feeling just a bit jealous of the playhouse, though, for now that you have it, what does that mean between you and me? I mean, I've heard of obsessed artists, after all, that give everything up for the theater. Am I going to become some kind of... acting widow?~
@502  = ~(Tashia growls good naturedly) Yeah, I know, I know, we aren't married at all, but you know what I mean.~
@503  = ~You don't need to worry about that. Plays really don't bring in a lot of money. What I was thinking of doing, though, was to put in some poles, hire some girls... And you know what, put a garland of flowers in your hair... you would probably be the largest draw. I mean, think of it, we could debut you as the Queen of Spring...~
@504  = ~Well, I wouldn't mind running another play when all is said and done. But in the meantime, the stage will not be used for a while... What would you say to hosting a round of riddles? If nothing else, many people wouldn't mind trying to sharpen their wits.~
@505  = ~I don't really know what I want to do. I won't deny that it is nice to have a place to call one's own, but who knows what the future holds? After all, I know that you said you wished to continue traveling, at least for the foreseeable future.I know that I easily see us being together there.~
@506  = ~(Her eyes following your gaze up and down her body, she reaches forward, grasping his jaw in her hand, her jade-green eyes turning a deeper green from her anger, and then she lets your jaw loose with a wrench, her fingers raising red welts on your face.)~
@507  = ~(She comes forward, takes a deep sniff, and growls) I don't smell any alcohol on your breath.~
@508  = ~(Tashia shakes her head, as she draws her arms in close, her foot tapping on the ground) So, what gave you this... brilliant brainstorm, anyway?~
@509  = ~(Shake your hand, and gently grab ahold of Tashia's hand, not exposing any other extremity to her rage) I was just joking Tashia, honest. I'm sorry. I wasn't being serious, I was just trying to lighten the mood up. Heh, sorry if it needed a bit more work. But the one thing I wasn't kidding about was how beautiful you are...~
@510  = ~Well, I mean it's all well and good to run a play, but do you know the final cost? The whole endeavor was running clear in the red. It is a damn wonder I didn't have to borrow some money elsewhere. But think of it this way. You and me, when this is all done, will be working side by side...~
@511  = ~(Tashia's anger subsides somewhat, and she tries to put on a sheepish grin, though she really is having a hard time doing so, and she ruffles your hair as you kiss her hand.)~
@512  = ~Okay, you had me believing you, you got me...~
@513  = ~(She grins, her eyes flashing) But if you want me to dance for you, you are going to have to dance for me...~
@514  = ~(Kissing your lips, she murmurs) But only for an audience of one. I don't like to share...~
@515  = ~(Tashia's anger grows deeper, and she says) If that's how you view me... well, better that I know than before we go any further.~
@516  = ~(Her hand rises rapidly, and slaps you a good one, leaving an angry red welt, as she finishes) And that's for thinking that I am some kind of whore.~
@517  = ~(Tashia's eyes light up, and she moves and plants her lips softly on yours, and for a brief moment you are lost in her tender kiss, when she pulls back and says) That is a sweet thought.~
@518  = ~(She tosses back her hair, and smiles, though she is a bit hesitant, as she adds) And I must admit that it would be nice to go somewhere, where our lives aren't hanging in the balance minute by minute.~
@519  = ~(Tashia pauses, and then adds) Or where even knowing a riddle can be the difference between life and death...~
@520  = ~(Tashia's lips quirk, and she scampers just a bit away and says) I'm told a certain something grows in its pouch, swells and stands up, lifts its covering. A proud bride grasped that boneless wonder, the daughter of a king covered that swollen thing with clothing...~
@521  = ~(Smile at her) Is it... bread dough?~
@522  = ~(Look at Tashia, and smile, as you decide to give a slight pelvic thrust, and say) Is it what I think it is?~
@523  = ~(Tashia's lips puff out as she feigns pouting, and then smiles) Damn. I thought for sure that you would miss that one.~
@524  = ~(She gives a lascivious wink, and then hungrily kisses you again, as she murmurs) I supposes it is a good thing that you can keep your... head... clear...~
@525  = ~(Tashia laughs, and she gives a gentle love tap on your face, as she says) I can see where your mind is at...~
@526  = ~(Giving a saucy leer, she answers) The answer was bread dough...~
@527  = ~(She licks her lips, and lays her hands at the top of your trousers as she whispers) But let's see if we can get rise out of something else...~
@528  = ~(Tashia smiles, and she strides forward and hugs you, saying) Well, I'm glad that whatever we decide to do, you see us doing it together.~
@529  = ~(She pushes the hair from your eyes) But while we are here, there is nothing wrong with enjoying the playhouse...~
@530  = ~(Tashia walks over to you, giving an appreciative 'Hmm...' as you feel her eyes peering over you, much like a woman eyeing a piece of meat in butcher's shop. Tashia circles around you before stopping.)~
@531  = ~(Her face breaks out in a grin, enjoying her slight teasing of you with her actions, and she says) I was expecting Lord <CHARNAME> to be a bit taller. You know, just like the heroes of legend. Seven feet tall, broad shouldered, thighs with which you can break tables, sloping forehead...~
@532  = ~(Tashia leans in then, and kisses your lips, her tongue teasingly darting forward before she steps back. Tashia grabs your hand in hers, and pressing it close to her heart, and says hesitantly) Pardon my teasing, <CHARNAME>. Between the hunt for Irenicus and all your additional duties protecting Nalia's birthright, you seem to be worn thin.~
@533  = ~(Rise up, and remove your hand from Tashia's, and say) That's right, I've been worn thin. People seem to think that I can go on and on, like I'm some kind of thoroughbred horse. And what do I have to show for it? I have people still asking for my help, and I have others snickering behind my back. Oh wait, I now have someone making fun of me in front of my face...~
@534  = ~(Smile at Tashia, and say) I guess that's so. Too many things going on. I apologize if I seemed distant. Perhaps you wouldn't mind telling me another of your riddles? I could use the distraction, and the excuse to see your perfect lips speak once more.~
@535  = ~(Grasp Tashia's right hand, bend on one knee, and brush your lips along the back of her knuckles) Fair Maiden, I have slain fearsome dragons, conquered mighty enemies, and braved unspeakable terrors, but next to a mere fleeting moment basking in thine angelic presence, these triumphs pale such as to disgrace my honor. Dear Lady, wilst thou save my honor and grant thy heavenly companionship to me?~
@536  = ~(Tashia looks up in your face, her jovial mood dissipated by the force of your emotion, clutching her hands at her side, not moving from her spot either.)~
@537  = ~(Concern crosses her face, and she embraces you tightly once more, and whispers into your ear) I am sorry, but I never laughed at you. I'm proud of all that you've accomplished, you know that.~
@538  = ~(She kisses you on the cheek, running her fingers through your arm hair, stroking and caressing your skin) Maybe no one else has told you this, but I'm proud of you. I'm sure that Gorion would have been proud of you too. Sometimes I forget how young you are.~
@539  = ~(Then she turns more serious, stroking your face with her index finger) But you're killing yourself with this pace. I know you don't have much choice now, but you need to slow down, the sooner the better.~
@540  = ~(Hold Tashia tight, and kiss her passionately) I love you, you know. You usually know the right thing to say. It it means a lot to me. That you are proud of me, I mean. And you're right, this pace is going to kill me. Heh, honestly, I don't really want power. I just object to idiots having power over me.~
@541  = ~(Look at Tashia, and answer sarcastically) Well, thank you for stating the obvious. I'm so glad that with all I've done, you are proud of me. I'm starting to think that maybe, just maybe, that is the way of the world. The only one you can rely on is yourself, and what you are able to hold in your two hands...~
@542  = ~(Tashia eagerly kisses you back, and she rests her head on your shoulder, and she murmurs in agreement with you.)~
@543  = ~(Tashia gently runs her fingers along the lines of your face, cupping your cheek with her hand, when she says) The one thing I've learned in my years: endure pain, find joy, and make your own meaning, because the world certainly isn't going to supply it.~
@544  = ~(Kissing the side of your neck, tasting the salt on your skin, she says) I guess that's why I'm so quick with a riddle, or a joke. Life is much too short to spend on continuous strife, worry, and sadness.~
@545  = ~(Twining the fingers of her right hand into yours, she steps back, and whispers) But I find joy with you no matter what.~
@546  = ~(Tashia looks stricken at your last comments, but rather than dwelling in sadness, she rises up and the mounting fury of her faces matches your anger.)~
@547  = ~Damn you, you... you bastard. I've heard this talk before, right before Arilistan kidnapped me, and killed me. Even in death he couldn't let me go.~
@548  = ~(Drawing herself up, she looks you straight in the eye, and practically shrieks) Well, I don't want your... love out of some damn sense of obligation. And don't worry, I will be sure not to be in your damn way in the future!~
@549  = ~(Tears slowly coming down her eyes, she growls) I hope you are happy grasping for power, for it's going to be a long, lonely life...~
@550  = ~(She sighs, and holding your hand in hers, she says) Very well. I am valued by men, fetched from afar, gleaned on the hill-slopes, gathered in groves, in dale and on down. All day through the air, wings bore me aloft, and brought me with cunning. Safe under roof, men steeped me in vats. Now I have power to pummel and bind, to cast to the earth, old man and young...~
@551  = ~Soon he shall find who reaches to seize me, pits force against force, that he's flat on the ground, stripped of his strength if he cease not his folly, loud in his speech, but of power despoiled to manage his mind, his hands or his feet. Now ask me my name, who can bind men on earth, and lay fools low in the light of day.~
@552  = ~Love, for just as you have claimed my heart, and laid me low, so can love do for any man.~
@553  = ~Is it mead or wine? For when drunk, it can lay the strongest man low?~
@554  = ~I don't know. What is it?~
@555  = ~(Tashia clenches your hands tightly in hers, a blush climbing over her face, and she says) It's not often that one who has said the wrong answer can still be so right...~
@556  = ~(She leans in, pressing her lips tightly to your mouth, creating a perfect seal so, for just that moment in time, the only thing you are aware of is the feel of her skin on yours, and the warmth of the breath you share, her long blond hair draping itself on your skin.)~
@557  = ~(When she pulls back, a pleasant flush on her face, she says) The answer was honey-mead, but your answer was sweeter than mine...~
@558  = ~(Tashia smiles, and she says) Indeed, it is mead actually, for it is made from honey, the wings that carry it being the flight of bees.~
@559  = ~(Tashia then leans in and kisses you, and as she presses her lips onto yours, you notice how especially sweet her lips are. Tashia then pulls back, and she lifts up a canteen, a sparkle in her eye as she presses it towards you. As you take a deep drought of it, the sweetness is almost too much on your tongue, but this is quickly forgotten as the heady brew makes its way down your gullet.)~
@560  = ~(Just as the brew hits your system, Tashia leans in again to give a kiss, and after another breath-gasping moment, you find that your head is abuzz, though whether due to the kiss or mead is another matter.)~
@561  = ~(She giggles) Sweets for the sweet...~
@562  = ~(Tashia shakes her head, and says) The answer is honey-mead.~
@563  = ~(She gives a pat on your head, and says) That's okay, you'll get it next time.~
@564  = ~(She gives a saucy swing of her hip, noticing the glint in your eye, and she laughs) At least you're preoccupied by something more important now...~
@565  = ~(Tashia catches her breath, and then she smiles, beckoning for you to stand and she gives you a gentle kiss on your cheek. )~
@566  = ~(She then steps back, caressing the side of your face with her hand, and then says, falling into the faux-antiquated language you were speaking earlier) I have faced powerful spirits, magical beasts, and evil men, but 'twas your eyes, m'lord, which finally smote me...~
@567  = ~(There is laughter dancing behind her eyes, and she snuggles firmly into your embrace.)~
@568  = ~(While Tashia lies within your embrace, you look toward the sky and say) I daresay I am up for another riddle. It has been a while since you sharpened your wit on me...~
@569  = ~(Decide to say another line for your beloved, but in a slightly different context) My dear lady, thou art the loveliest creature that hath ever had the generosity to grace our poor, beleaguered world. Thy radiance far outshines that of the sun, moon, and all the stars in the night sky. Now grab your ankles...~
@570  = ~(Tashia seems lost in your words, but at your very last phrase, she starts to laugh, holding you tight to her body.)~
@571  = ~(She peppers your face with kisses, saying) I was wondering how long you could keep that up...~
@572  = ~(A sultry look crosses her face, as she briefly hitches up the side of her skirt, exposing an ankle, and leans provocatively into you, saying) You've broken down my battlements, sirrah and laid siege to my heart...~
@573  = ~(You feel a pair of slender arms wrap around you from behind, and the press of Tashia's head as she leans into your backside) Hmm. You feel real enough to me...~
@574  = ~(She steps in front of you, and there is a smile playing at her lips, as she explains her cryptic remark) Heh. Sorry, I was just thinking of all that you've done. You have managed to defeat a great evil, gained said evil's base of operations, and even managed to make peace with the Cowled Wizards... or some members of it. If I didn't know better, I would have thought someone was just making up a bit of a far-fetched story; that you were a tall tale...~
@575  = ~(Pausing, Tashia changes the conversation and chuckles) So what are you going to do about that grey big iron ball? I wonder if Lavok had some kind of physical issues he was trying to work through...~
@576  = ~Well, I don't know, but since it seems I have the tacit acceptance of some of the Cowled Wizards, I might decide to go into business for myself. There has to be some good money there, somewhere. What I really need is something that is unique...~
@577  = ~Well, now that I think of it, I may continue where Lavok faltered. I think I know just where he went wrong... and with your help, and your magical prowess, I really think that we can succeed where he failed. Just think of it. Eternal life and none of this lich nonsense...~
@578  = ~I don't really know, I figured that at least for the immediate future I would be traveling, with you of course. Maybe I should just rent it out. True, it is not in a prime location, but the fact that the place is practically fireproof, at least on the outside, should count for something...~
@579  = ~(Tashia quirks an eyebrow, and she asks) And what do you mean by... unique?~
@580  = ~(Cup one of Tashia's breasts and placing a hand on her buttocks) Well, the answer is obvious! Magic for cosmetic alterations! We already have illusions to disguise oneself, but those are ultimately fleeting, but I would bet that with just a few alteration spells we could easily corner the market. Just think what we could do with a few Growth spells!~
@581  = ~I guess I don't really have a good idea. Maybe it was just a stupid thing to say. I mean, every time some magician gets beyond the stage of doing party tricks, they always seem to end up in some kind of tower, or being a hermit in some damn cave, and that's assuming they don't go nuts in general.~
@582  = ~Well, truth be known, I was thinking that we could open up some kind of joke shop. Heh, I remember an old joke that Imoen played on me. She found this old bladder, it may have been a cow, but I don't know... and she placed it under my chair as dinner time rolled around, I went to sit. Well, Gorion thought I... expelled some gas. But just think, if we combine that with some kind of low level Stinking Cloud spell, maybe a cantrip even an apprentice could learn...~
@583  = ~(Tashia gives a shriek, and you suddenly find yourself gasping for breath as Tashia brings a sharp elbow up into your midsection, and with a second strike aims her elbow just a bit lower, catching you square in the groin.)~
@584  = ~(She growls) How dare you touch me like that?  And before you start suggesting that women would be receptive for some kind of... augmentation, you might take a look at your own shortcomings...~
@585  = ~(Tashia steps forward, embracing you in her arms, and she says) I'm sorry, I didn't mean to ruin the mood.~
@586  = ~(She leans in and gives a kiss on your forehead, and adds) But the fact that you are concerned about that is a good sign.~
@587  = ~(Tashia smiles, as she whispers) And you know, if that's all anyone does, doing party tricks... well, as long as they are happy, there isn't exactly anything wrong with that.~
@588  = ~(Tashia gives a reassuring hug, and then whispers) Whatever else happens, I'm just happy being with you.~
@589  = ~(Tashia's eyes crinkle, hiding the laughter that she is restraining but at the last moment she guffaws, and says) Imoen... did that to you? Why do I have the feeling that many of the products might actually come from things you suffered from her?~
@590  = ~(Tashia shakes her head, and then leans in to kiss you tenderly on the cheek, saying) But I think it's sweet that you can laugh at yourself, unlike...~
@591  = ~(Tashia grows silent, and she whispers) Unlike Arilistan...~
@592  = ~(The silence grows, and then Tashia shakes her long hair loose, and says) Well, come what may, that does sound like an interesting idea...~
@593  = ~(Tashia's face contorts with horror, and she pulls away from you, screaming) You... you beast...~
@594  = ~(She maintains a suitable distance from you, and continues) How can you even entertain such thoughts?~
@595  = ~(Tashia continues to eye you, sudden anger and fear continuing to infuse her face, and she says) Maybe it's the taint within you talking, maybe it's not, but to forget all that we've gone through...~
@596  = ~(She shakes her head sadly, as she makes her way to the edge of the party, and whispers) I don't know...how you could consider something so abhorrent... and frankly, I don't give care to find out. (and she darts away...)~
@597  = ~(Tashia laughs, and she says) Well, I guess you're right. That is definitely something you can do.~
@598  = ~(She pauses and says) You know, though... if you decide to only rent to halflings and gnomes, then you could certainly get more money out of the structure than if you rented to humans. You know, be known as a low-rent place.~
@599  = ~(Tashia shrugs, and says) Sorry, I know that was a bit of a stretch.~
@600  = ~(She reaches forward, and taps your nose, and says) Whatever you decide, it will be fine, I'm sure.~
@601  = ~(Tashia looks at the forest around her, closes her eyes, and takes a deep breath, the tension of your travels eases from her face. When she opens her eyes again, there is a smile tugging at her lips, and she says) You know, in the hustle and bustle of our travels, in the drudgery of trudging around, it is just nice to take one's ease.~
@602  = ~(Tashia gives a small smile, her eyes looking a bit demurely toward you, and then she says) It is kind of liberating being out here, where no one is looking at you, where there are no other expectations except for what you place on yourself.~
@603  = ~(She laughs then, and says) Well, I guess you would know better than I would. After all, you were the one to become a druid, and a Great Druid at that. Doing rather well, if I can keep the stories in place.~
@604  = ~(Tashia gives a small, pleasant sigh, and then she asks) So what are you up to?~
@605  = ~Oh, nothing important. Just thinking. You are right, you know, it's much nicer here in the woods, away from the noise of the cities. Heh, I guess it's no wonder that I was so eager to leave Candlekeep. All those moldy books, the stone walls. The loremasters thought they were protecting themselves, yet, they can't seem to see that they were also imprisoning themselves. Sorry, I guess you didn't come here to listen to a lecture, but I just find myself at ease with you...~
@606  = ~(Bend down on your knees, and push some buds and dark grasses away, plucking a few up) Oh, just doing a little grubbing, you know. Herbs and stuff. No reason to waste magic on something that a simple poultice or potion would do.~
@607  = ~I didn't really have anything planned. Just enjoying being out in nature, I guess, nothing more, nothing less. Why don't you tell me a riddle instead. We have some time to kill, and I do enjoy your mind-twisters.~
@608  = ~Nothing really important. However, if it's not to much, can we proceed along in silence?~
@609  = ~(Tashia embraces you from behind, resting her head on your shoulder. As she looks out at the woods with you, a faint scent of rose reaches your nose, indicating Tashia must be trying a new type of perfume.)~
@610  = ~(Tashia's smile grows a bit larger, and she says) Oh? And just what were you thinking about?~
@611  = ~Faldorn, mostly. No matter what else transpired, she was a druid much like I am. I brought about her defeat, but what if in the long run she was right? I would be lying if I didn't admit if I can't see where she was coming from after all...~
@612  = ~(Grin widely, and prepare to duck) Oh deep thoughts. You know the type, like if a man yells in the woods and no woman hears him, is he still wrong?~
@613  = ~(Laugh) Damn, now you made me forget what I was thinking about. Ah well, it wasn't anything really important anyway...~
@614  = ~(Tashia nods, and she steps in close, embracing you, trying to lift your spirits with her presence, and she whispers) For what it is worth, I don't think that you will be like Faldorn.~
@615  = ~(Grasping your hand, she leans in and kisses the joint of your shoulder and neck) Try not to dwell on it too much, love. That can be just as bad as not considering it either.~
@616  = ~(Tashia just stands by your side, comforting you in silence.)~
@617  = ~(Tashia laughs, and she gives you a light cuff on the head) Well, I guess that will teach me to ask a serious question of you.~
@618  = ~(Her eyes glow with laughter as she asks) But seriously, what are you up to?~
@619  = ~Well, why don't you tell me a riddle. It has been a while since we last did one.~
@620  = ~I was just thinking of gathering some herbs. Hmm... I have a brew that you may care to try.~
@621  = ~Actually, if you don't mind too much, I would just like some time alone. It has been a while since I communed with Nature...~
@622  = ~(Tashia laughs, and she says) Well, I can honestly say I wasn't expecting that answer.~
@623  = ~(She peers curiously at the pouch, and caresses your hand, as she asks) So, just what are you able to make with those plants?~
@624  = ~(Glancing at Tashia's lithe but attractive elven form, you see that her body shows the signs of fatigue) ell you what. I'm going to make something that is bound to make you feel better...~
@625  = ~(Glancing at Tashia's lithe but attractive elven form, you feel your libido rise and decide to make an aphrodisiac) Tell you what. I'm going to make something that is bound to make you feel better...~
@626  = ~Tashia, please, leave me alone. This is hard enough without someone interrupting me. I promise that if there is some time afterward, I will spend it with you. But until then, I really need to concentrate...~
@627  = ~(Tashia drinks the mixture, and her face winces as the foul tasting brew first hits her tongue, but seeing the comforting nod from you, she drinks the entire brew, and then sighs as she whispers) My aches, mypains... they're fading.~
@628  = ~(She gives a furtive yawn, and says) That's an excellent recipe, but you really should figure out something to discharge that awful taste.~
@629  = ~(Her face positively glowing, she leans into you, and wraps her arms around your waist, leaning in to nuzzle your neck, adding) Hmm... I think that I can use some relaxation, tonight...~
@630  = ~(Tashia takes the beverage, and takes a tentative sip, saying) Say, this is good. Really good.~
@631  = ~(She upends the cup and leans in close to you, whispering) Hmm... everything feels funny. It... it feels like there is a buzzing on my insides. My loins feel...~
@632  = ~(Tashia licks her lips as she looks at you, and she grabs your hand, pulling you away from the edges of the party and down into the bushes with her.)~
@633  = ~(As time passes, you emerge from the bushes, bare to the waist, and you feel small rivulets of warm blood flowing down your cool back. Tashia rises as well, but this time there is fury on her face, her fingernails still bloody, pulling her own clothes around her.)~
@634  = ~(She shouts) You... you bastard! You son of a bitch! You drugged me! Why?~
@635  = ~(She howls to the sky, her fury and betrayal plain on her face) Why?!?~
@636  = ~(Tears streaming down her face, she gathers her belongings, and races off into the wilderness, and out of your life.)~
@637  = ~(Tashia clears her throat, and a look of devilment crosses her face, as she says)
I am a wondrous creature: to women a thing of joyful expectation, to close-lying companions serviceable. 
I harm no city-dweller excepting my slayer alone. My stem is erect and tall--I stand up in bed--and whiskery somewhere down below. 
Sometimes a countryman's quite comely daughter will venture, bumptious girl, to get a grip on me. 
She assaults my red self and seizes my head and clenches me in a cramped place. 
She will soon feel the effect of her encounter with me, this curl-locked woman who squeezes me. 
Her eye will be wet... what am I?~
@638  = ~Are you perchance a thorny rose?~
@639  = ~Are you perchance an onion, one that makes a lady cry?~
@640  = ~(Smile, as you know Tashia quite well, and take one of her hand's, and insert it into your trousers, letting Tashia feel around) Is this the answer?~
@641  = ~(Tashia's large smile tells you that you are correct, and she says) Hmm... I really need to find some hard ones, or else you remembered this one from before, the thorn of the rose piercing the fingers of the young maiden, bringing tears to her eyes.~
@642  = ~(She puts her arms around your neck, and draws your head down near hers, and when she kisses you, running the tip of her tongue along her lips, you taste strawberry on Tashia's lips.)~
@643  = ~(As she pulls back, Tashia runs a hand along your cheek, and you see red stains on her fingertips, and her eyes twinkle) I guess its only fair that in light of your herblore that I share the wild strawberries I found earlier...~
@644  = ~(Tashia giggles, and says) Since when is an onion red?~
@645  = ~(She leans in, and kisses you tenderly on the cheek, before pulling apart, saying) I guess even master druids can be wrong at times.~
@646  = ~(Tashia squeezes your hand, and whispers) But you've won the consolation prize... (and she kisses you full on the lips.)~
@647  = ~(Tashia's eyes open wide at your effrontery, and she clenches her right hand, sending waves of pain shooting through your body while a stray thought at the back of your mind admires Tashia's grip.)~
